<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFEA3932EBD2C68AFE13597D" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFEA3932EBD2C68AFEA35AE5" blockId="68.[227,348,441,467]" box="[227,348,441,467]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<heading id="5A24A609FFEA3932EBD2C68AFEA35AE5" bold="true" box="[227,348,441,467]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFEA3932EBD2C68AFEA35AE5" bold="true" box="[227,348,441,467]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFEA3932EBD2C6DAFE13597D" blockId="68.[226,1439,489,587]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">OL/OH = 1.03–1.33, OsL/CaL = 0.83–1.20. Circular otoliths with small, pointed but well-developed rostrum and antirostrum. Shape of posterior rim varies markedly among specimens. Sulcus well divided into ostium and cauda.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFEA3932EBD2C547FBA0598B" box="[227,1119,628,702]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFEA3932EBD2C547FE9559B8" blockId="68.[227,362,628,654]" box="[227,362,628,654]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<heading id="5A24A609FFEA3932EBD2C547FE9559B8" bold="true" box="[227,362,628,654]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFEA3932EBD2C547FE9559B8" bold="true" box="[227,362,628,654]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFEA3932EBD2C590FBA0598B" blockId="68.[227,1119,675,702]" box="[227,1119,675,702]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">The name alludes to the considerable intraspecific variability of the otoliths.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
